Author-Name: MATTHEW RICHARDSON 
Author-Name: MICHAEL R. ROBERTS 
Title: On the Importance of Measuring Payout Yield: Implications for Empirical Asset Pricing 
Abstract:
 We investigate the empirical implications of using various measures of
 payout yield rather than dividend yield for asset pricing models. We find
 statistically and economically significant predictability in the time
 series when payout (dividends plus repurchases) and net payout (dividends
 plus repurchases minus issuances) yields are used instead of the dividend
 yield. Similarly, we find that payout (net payout) yields contains
 information about the cross section of expected stock returns exceeding
 that of dividend yields, and that the high minus low payout yield
 portfolio is a priced factor. Copyright 2007 by The American Finance Association. 
